Privacy coins are really what crypto was meant to be in the early-stages and just as #Bitcoin, they will always have a use case (#Anonymity is demanded more than ever before).
But it's just the "institutionalization" of $BTC that will create strong selling pressure.

In terms of more regulation, #Bitcoin will face more selling pressure than privacy coins. 
This will mainly come from fear of exchange delistings and institutions dumping their $BTC (They don't buy it to use it, but to use it as an investment).
$BTC was born in a crisis to provide an alternative to the centralized banking system. Today, #Bitcoin is increasingly held by these institutions, which it was supposed to replace.
